        "content": [
          {
            "Text": "[Thu 2026-04-23 10:21 PDT] Create a new file `war-room.html` — an interactive Agent War Room / Incident Command Center page for the AgentBox marketing site.\n\nThis is a STATIC HTML page (no server needed) with embedded CSS and JS, matching the site's dark theme style. Look at `index.html` for the site's nav/footer patterns and color scheme (dark background, gradients, accent colors).\n\n## What to build:\n\nAn interactive simulation of a multi-agent incident command center with these features:\n\n### 1. Incident Board\n- A status board showing the current incident (auto-generated scenarios like \"API Latency Spike\", \"Database Connection Pool Exhausted\", \"Auth Service 503\", \"Memory Leak Detected\", \"Certificate Expiring\")\n- Severity indicator (SEV-1 through SEV-4) with color coding\n- Incident timer showing duration\n- Current phase indicator (Detection → Triage → Mitigation → Recovery → Resolved)\n\n### 2. Agent Team Panel\n- Show 5-6 agents with roles: Incident Commander, Communications Lead, Diagnostics Agent, Mitigation Agent, Monitoring Agent, Scribe\n- Each agent has a name, avatar emoji, role badge, and status (idle/investigating/acting/reporting)\n- Agents autonomously take actions based on the incident phase (simulated with timers)\n\n### 3. Live Action Timeline\n- A scrolling timeline of agent actions with timestamps\n- Color-coded by agent role\n- Actions include: \"Running diagnostics...\", \"Identified root cause: connection pool leak\", \"Applying fix: increasing pool size\", \"Notifying stakeholders\", \"Monitoring recovery metrics\"\n- Auto-populates as the simulation runs\n\n### 4. Metrics Panel\n- 3-4 live-updating metric cards with Canvas sparklines\n- Metrics: Response Time (ms), Error Rate (%), CPU Usage (%), Active Connections\n- During incident: metrics degrade; during mitigation: they recover\n- Sparkline shows last 30 data points\n\n### 5. Autonomous Escalation\n- If metrics don't improve within a threshold, auto-escalation triggers\n- Visual alert when escalation happens\n- Escalation adds a new agent or increases severity\n\n### 6. Controls\n- \"New Incident\" button to start a fresh scenario\n- Speed control (1x, 2x, 5x)\n- Pause/Resume\n- Manual escalation button\n\n### Style Guidelines:\n- Dark theme matching the site (bg ~#0a0a0a or #1a1a2e, cards with subtle borders)\n- Use the site's gradient accents (purple/blue/cyan)\n- Smooth animations for timeline entries\n- Responsive layout\n- Include the site's standard nav bar and footer (copy from another page like simulator.html)\n- Page title: \"Agent War Room — AgentBox\"\n\n### Technical:\n- Single self-contained HTML file with inline CSS and JS\n- Use Canvas API for sparklines\n- No external dependencies beyond what the site already uses\n- All simulation logic runs client-side with setInterval/setTimeout\n\nKeep the file under 35KB. Focus on making the simulation feel alive and autonomous — agents should appear to think and act independently.\n\nAfter creating the file, verify with: `node -c war-room.html 2>&1 || echo \"Not a JS file, checking HTML structure\"; Select-String -Pattern \"</html>\" war-room.html`\n\nDo NOT create any git commits. Do NOT push. Just create the file."
          }
        ]
      }
